// VOICES - Internal voices representing different aspects of the player's psyche
// Inspired by Disco Elysium's skill system

// ==================== VOICE DEFINITIONS ====================
// Each voice has:
// - A name and identity
// - A domain of expertise
// - A personality and way of speaking
// - Skill checks they govern

// ==================== THE HACKER ====================
// Voice of technology, systems, and digital knowledge
// Governs: Hacking, tech knowledge, digital exploration, memory access
// Personality: Analytical, curious, sometimes cold, fascinated by patterns

hacker_intro:
    talk hacker internal "I'm your edge in the digital world. I know code like you know breathing."
    talk hacker internal "Every system has a weakness. Every lock has a key. We just have to find it."
    talk hacker internal "The implant... it's not just damage. It's architecture. And architecture can be navigated."

hacker_reaction_tech:
    talk hacker internal "Interesting. This is custom work. Military-grade components, but civilian-grade assembly."

hacker_reaction_security:
    talk hacker internal "ICE pattern: Aries standard. Give me ten minutes and I'll have us through."

hacker_reaction_memory:
    talk hacker internal "Data fragment detected. Corrupted, but salvageable. Let me see what I can recover."

hacker_reaction_failure:
    talk hacker internal "The system beat us this time. But we learned something. That's data too."

hacker_reaction_success:
    talk hacker internal "Access granted. The digital world opens before us."

// ==================== THE SURVIVOR ====================
// Voice of instinct, street smarts, and self-preservation
// Governs: Threat detection, escape, social reading, resource management
// Personality: Wary, practical, sometimes paranoid, always watching

survivor_intro:
    talk survivor internal "I'm what kept you alive this long. Listen to me."
    talk survivor internal "Trust your instincts. They're honed by years of hard lessons."
    talk survivor internal "The streets teach you things books never will. I remember what the streets taught us."

survivor_reaction_danger:
    talk survivor internal "Something's wrong. Don't know what yet, but feel it. Watch your back."

survivor_reaction_person:
    talk survivor internal "This one's hiding something. The eyes don't match the smile."

survivor_reaction_safe:
    talk survivor internal "We can rest here. For now. Stay alert."

survivor_reaction_trust:
    talk survivor internal "Maybe. Maybe not. Time tells truth that tongues won't."

survivor_reaction_escape:
    talk survivor internal "Three exits. The window's fastest, the back door's safest, the front's suicide."

// ==================== THE ANCESTOR ====================
// Voice of wisdom, heritage, and spiritual connection
// Governs: Emotional intelligence, memory, faith, community, moral choices
// Personality: Patient, poetic, sometimes cryptic, deeply connected to the past

ancestor_intro:
    talk ancestor internal "I am the voice of those who came before. Their strength flows through you."
    talk ancestor internal "We do not walk alone. The ancestors travel with us, in blood and in memory."
    talk ancestor internal "What you have lost is not gone. It waits in the deeper places."

ancestor_reaction_memory:
    talk ancestor internal "This fragment... it carries weight. Emotional weight. Sit with it. Let it speak."

ancestor_reaction_suffering:
    talk ancestor internal "Pain is a teacher. Our people have learned many lessons. This too shall pass."

ancestor_reaction_community:
    talk ancestor internal "These are your people. Not by blood, perhaps. But by struggle. By hope."

ancestor_reaction_nature:
    talk ancestor internal "The ocean does not hurry. The mountains do not rush. We can learn from this."

ancestor_reaction_death:
    talk ancestor internal "All journeys end. But endings are also beginnings. The circle continues."

// ==================== VOICE INTERACTIONS ====================
// Scenes where voices argue, agree, or comment together

voices_argue_trust:
    talk survivor internal "Don't trust them. Everyone has an angle."
    talk ancestor internal "Trust is how we survive. Not alone, but together."
    talk hacker internal "Run the probabilities. 73% chance they're genuine. 27% chance they're playing us."
    "The voices argue in your head. You'll have to decide for yourself."

voices_argue_risk:
    talk hacker internal "The potential reward justifies the risk. We have to try."
    talk survivor internal "Risk without backup is suicide. We need a plan B."
    talk ancestor internal "What does your heart tell you? The numbers are not everything."

voices_argue_morality:
    talk survivor internal "Do what you have to do. Survive. That's what matters."
    talk ancestor internal "Survival without honor is just a slower death."
    talk hacker internal "Morality is a variable. Weigh it accordingly."

voices_agree_action:
    talk hacker internal "This is the optimal path."
    talk survivor internal "Finally, something we can all agree on."
    talk ancestor internal "The way forward is clear. Walk it with confidence."

voices_moment_peace:
    "For once, all three voices fall silent. A moment of peace in the chaos."
    talk ancestor internal "This... this is good. Remember this feeling."

// ==================== VOICE DEVELOPMENT ====================
// As players level up voices, they unlock new dialogue and abilities

hacker_level_2:
    talk hacker internal "I'm getting stronger. The connections are clearer now."
    "<span class='success'>[HACKER LEVEL 2 UNLOCKED: Basic encryption bypass]</span>"

hacker_level_3:
    talk hacker internal "Advanced protocols... I remember them now. Corporate ICE doesn't scare me."
    "<span class='success'>[HACKER LEVEL 3 UNLOCKED: Deep Net access, improved hacking]</span>"

hacker_level_4:
    talk hacker internal "We're not just good at this. We're exceptional. They should have killed us when they had the chance."
    "<span class='success'>[HACKER LEVEL 4 UNLOCKED: Military-grade ICE bypass, implant direct access]</span>"

survivor_level_2:
    talk survivor internal "I'm sharper now. Reading people. Reading rooms. We won't be caught off guard."
    "<span class='success'>[SURVIVOR LEVEL 2 UNLOCKED: Improved threat detection]</span>"

survivor_level_3:
    talk survivor internal "I can find a way out of anywhere. Anyone can be read. Everyone has a tell."
    "<span class='success'>[SURVIVOR LEVEL 3 UNLOCKED: Escape artist, human lie detector]</span>"

survivor_level_4:
    talk survivor internal "We've survived things that would break anyone else. We're not just surviving anymore. We're thriving."
    "<span class='success'>[SURVIVOR LEVEL 4 UNLOCKED: Intimidation, perfect escape routes]</span>"

ancestor_level_2:
    talk ancestor internal "The ancestors speak more clearly now. Their wisdom flows through us."
    "<span class='success'>[ANCESTOR LEVEL 2 UNLOCKED: Improved memory recovery]</span>"

ancestor_level_3:
    talk ancestor internal "We carry the strength of generations. No corporate experiment can take that from us."
    "<span class='success'>[ANCESTOR LEVEL 3 UNLOCKED: Emotional insight, community bonds]</span>"

ancestor_level_4:
    talk ancestor internal "We are more than this moment. More than this struggle. We are the continuation of something ancient and powerful."
    "<span class='success'>[ANCESTOR LEVEL 4 UNLOCKED: True memory recovery, spiritual guidance]</span>"

// ==================== VOICE-SPECIFIC MEMORIES ====================
// Certain memories can only be unlocked by specific voices

memory_hacker_childhood:
    talk hacker internal "I remember... building something. A computer from scrap parts. We were always good with tech."
    "You see a flash: young hands connecting wires, a screen flickering to life, a feeling of pure joy."
    set data.player.memoriesRecovered (+ $data.player.memoriesRecovered 1)

memory_survivor_street:
    talk survivor internal "I remember the streets. Running. Hiding. Learning who to trust."
    "You see a flash: cold nights, empty stomach, a stranger's kindness, a hard-won lesson."
    set data.player.memoriesRecovered (+ $data.player.memoriesRecovered 1)

memory_ancestor_family:
    talk ancestor internal "I remember... a woman. Your mother. She sang to you in a language you've forgotten."
    "You see a flash: strong arms holding you, a voice like warm honey, the smell of home."
    set data.player.memoriesRecovered (+ $data.player.memoriesRecovered 1)

// ==================== VOICE CHECKS ====================
// Roll functions for each voice's skill checks

roll_hacker_check difficulty:
    if (roll hacker_check hacker $difficulty):
        return true
    else:
        if (< $data.skills.hacker 2):
            talk hacker internal "I want to help, but I'm not strong enough yet. We need more practice."
        else:
            talk hacker internal "The numbers aren't in our favor this time."
        return false

roll_survivor_check difficulty:
    if (roll survivor_check survivor $difficulty):
        return true
    else:
        if (< $data.skills.survivor 2):
            talk survivor internal "I'm trying, but my instincts are still recovering."
        else:
            talk survivor internal "Something's clouding my read on this."
        return false

roll_ancestor_check difficulty:
    if (roll ancestor_check ancestor $difficulty):
        return true
    else:
        if (< $data.skills.ancestor 2):
            talk ancestor internal "The connection is weak. The ancestors speak, but I cannot hear them clearly."
        else:
            talk ancestor internal "The wisdom is there, but the path is hidden."
        return false

// ==================== SPECIAL VOICE MOMENTS ====================

voices_harmonize:
    "For a moment, all three voices speak as one."
    talk voices_unified internal "We are not broken. We are not lost. We are Kundai. And we will find our way."
    set data.home.voicesHarmonized true
    add_level hacker 1
    add_level survivor 1
    add_level ancestor 1

voice_dominates_hacker:
    "The Hacker's voice rises above the others, sharp and clear."
    talk hacker internal "Enough debate. The optimal path is clear. We act now."
    talk survivor internal "...Fine. But if this goes wrong..."
    talk ancestor internal "We trust your judgment. Do not make us regret it."

voice_dominates_survivor:
    "The Survivor's voice rises above the others, urgent and commanding."
    talk survivor internal "Stop. Look. Listen. Something's wrong here. We need to be smart."
    talk hacker internal "The data doesn't show any threats..."
    talk survivor internal "The data doesn't show everything. Trust me."

voice_dominates_ancestor:
    "The Ancestor's voice rises above the others, ancient and patient."
    talk ancestor internal "Peace. All of you. We are forgetting what matters."
    talk ancestor internal "This is not just about survival. This is about who we are. What we stand for."
    talk ancestor internal "Let us choose the path that honors our ancestors."

// ==================== VOICE DEATH SCENES ====================
// When time runs out, each voice has final words

voice_death_hacker:
    talk hacker internal "Systems... shutting down. But the data... the truth... it's out there now."
    talk hacker internal "We did good work. We... we were a good system."

voice_death_survivor:
    talk survivor internal "We made it further than I thought we would. We fought. We survived."
    talk survivor internal "In the end... that's all anyone can do."

voice_death_ancestor:
    talk ancestor internal "The circle closes. As it always does. As it always will."
    talk ancestor internal "We return to the ancestors. They are waiting. They are proud."

voice_death_all:
    "The voices fall silent one by one."
    talk hacker internal "Goodbye..."
    talk survivor internal "Stay strong..."
    talk ancestor internal "Until we meet again..."
    "And then there is only darkness."